---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="How to Vote - Autario Votes - Simcoe County"
  description="Learn about the voting process, registration, and important deadlines"
>
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>How to Vote</h1>
    
    <section>
      <h2>1. Register to Vote</h2>
      <p>
        To vote in the upcoming election, you must be registered. The registration deadline is 
        <strong>October 15, 2026</strong>.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You must be 18 years old by Election Day</li>
        <li>You must be a resident of the municipality where you're registering</li>
        <li>Register online, by mail, or in person at your local election office</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="#" class="link-button">Check Your Registration Status →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Know Your Voting Options</h2>
      
      <div class="options-grid">
        <div class="option-card">
          <h3>Vote Early</h3>
          <p><strong>TBA</strong></p>
          <p>Visit any early voting location during the early voting period. No excuse needed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="option-card">
          <h3>Vote by Mail</h3>
          <p><strong>TBA</strong></p>
          <p>Request an absentee ballot and mail it back. Must be postmarked by Election Day.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="option-card">
          <h3>Vote on Election Day</h3>
          <p><strong>October 26, 2026</strong></p>
          <p>Vote at your assigned polling location. Bring a valid photo ID.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. What to Bring</h2>
      <p>When you go to vote, bring one of the following forms of ID:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Driver's license</li>
        <li>Canadian passport</li>
        <li>Military ID</li>
        <li>Indian status card</li>
        <li>Birth certificate</li>
        <li>Health card</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Find Your Polling Location</h2>
      <p>
        Your polling location is assigned based on your address. Enter your address below to 
        find where you should vote.
      </p>
      <p><a href="#" class="link-button">Find My Polling Place →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Need Help?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about voting or need assistance, contact us at <a href="mailto:info@autvotes.ca">info@autvotes.ca</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .options-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .option-card {
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .option-card p {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>